rder-l-2 pl-5","style":{"borderColor":"#ff4d6d60"},"children":"Shipping an NLP model that demos well in a Jupyter notebook is the easy part. Making it survive real traffic, malformed inputs, and Monday-morning spikes — that's where real engineering begins. Here's how I think about building NLP pipelines that are actually production-ready."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-8","children":[["$","span","Flask",{"className":"text-xs px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full font-medium","style":{"color":"#ff4d6d","background":"#ff4d6d10","border":"1px solid #ff4d6d25"},"children":"Flask"}],["$","span","NLP",{"className":"text-xs px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full font-medium","style":{"color":"#ff4d6d","background":"#ff4d6d10","border":"1px solid #ff4d6d25"},"children":"NLP"}],["$","span","Python",{"className":"text-xs px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full font-medium","style":{"color":"#ff4d6d","background":"#ff4d6d10","border":"1px solid #ff4d6d25"},"children":"Python"}],["$","span","Production",{"className":"text-xs px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full font-medium","style":{"color":"#ff4d6d","background":"#ff4d6d10","border":"1px solid #ff4d6d25"},"children":"Production"}],["$","span","spaCy",{"className":"text-xs px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full font-medium","style":{"color":"#ff4d6d","background":"#ff4d6d10","border":"1px solid #ff4d6d25"},"children":"spaCy"}],["$","span","REST API",{"className":"text-xs px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full font-medium","style":{"color":"#ff4d6d","background":"#ff4d6d10","border":"1px solid #ff4d6d25"},"children":"REST API"}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"h-px w-full mb-12 opacity-20","style":{"background":"linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, #ff4d6d, transparent)"}}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-10","children":[["$","section","1. Start with a Clear Data Contract",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-5 leading-snug","children":"1. Start with a Clear Data Contract"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","div","0",{"children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"text-white/65 text-[15px] leading-[1.85] mb-4","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Before writing a single model call, define what your API accepts and returns. NLP endpoints fail in production because engineers skip this step and then argue about encoding issues for days."}}],null]}],["$","div","1",{"className":"relative my-6 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden border border-white/8","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-1.5 px-4 py-2.5 bg-white/4 border-b border-white/6","children":[["$","span","0",{"className":"w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full","style":{"background":"#ff5f56"}}],["$","span","1",{"className":"w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full","style":{"background":"#ffbd2e"}}],["$","span","2",{"className":"w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full","style":{"background":"#27c93f"}}]]}],["$","pre",null,{"className":"overflow-x-auto p-5 text-xs leading-relaxed text-white/75 font-mono bg-[#0d0d18]","children":["$","code",null,{"children":"# schemas.py\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\nfrom typing import Optional\n\n@dataclass\nclass AnalysisRequest:\n    text: str\n    language: str = \"en\"\n    max_tokens: Optional[int] = 512\n\n@dataclass\nclass AnalysisResponse:\n    sentiment: str          # \"positive\" | \"negative\" | \"neutral\"\n    confidence: float       # 0.0 – 1.0\n    keywords: list[str]\n    processing_ms: int"}]}]]}],["$","div","2",{"children":[null,["$","p","1",{"className":"text-white/65 text-[15px] leading-[1.85] mb-4","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Your schema is your contract. Validate every incoming request against it before the model ever sees the data."}}]]}]]}]]}],["$","section","2. Build a Preprocessing Pipeline, Not a Chain of Functions",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-5 leading-snug","children":"2. Build a Preprocessing Pipeline, Not a Chain of Functions"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","div","0",{"children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"text-white/65 text-[15px] leading-[1.85] mb-4","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"One of the most common mistakes I see is preprocessing logic scattered across route handlers. The moment you need to reuse or test any step, you're copy-pasting. Instead, build a composable pipeline:"}}],null]}],["$","div","1",{"className":"relative my-6 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden border border-white/8","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-1.5 px-4 py-2.5 bg-white/4 border-b border-white/6","children":[["$","span","0",{"className":"w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full","style":{"background":"#ff5f56"}}],["$","span","1",{"className":"w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full","style":{"background":"#ffbd2e"}}],["$","span","2",{"className":"w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full","style":{"background":"#27c93f"}}]]}],["$","pre",null,{"className":"overflow-x-auto p-5 text-xs leading-relaxed text-white/75 font-mono bg-[#0d0d18]","children":["$","code",null,{"children":"class TextPipeline:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.steps = []\n\n    def add(self, fn):\n        self.steps.append(fn)\n        return self  # enables chaining\n\n    def run(self, text: str) -> str:\n        for step in self.steps:\n            text = step(text)\n        return text\n\n# Usage\npipeline = (\n    TextPipeline()\n    .add(lambda t: t.lower().strip())\n    .add(remove_urls)\n    .add(normalize_unicode)\n    .add(remove_stopwords)\n)"}]}]]}],["$","div","2",{"children":[null,["$","p","1",{"className":"text-white/65 text-[15px] leading-[1.85] mb-4","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Each step is independently testable. Adding or removing a preprocessing stage takes one line."}}]]}]]}]]}],["$","section","3. Model Loading: Do It Once, Do It Right",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-5 leading-snug","children":"3. Model Loading: Do It Once, Do It Right"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","div","0",{"children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"text-white/65 text-[15px] leading-[1.85] mb-4","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Loading a spaCy model or a HuggingFace tokenizer on every request is a silent killer. It looks fine locally and destroys you at scale."}}],null]}],["$","div","1",{"className":"relative my-6 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden border border-white/8","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-1.5 px-4 py-2.5 bg-white/4 border-b border-white/6","children":[["$","span","0",{"className":"w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full","style":{"background":"#ff5f56"}}],["$","span","1",{"className":"w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full","style":{"background":"#ffbd2e"}}],["$","span","2",{"className":"w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full","style":{"background":"#27c93f"}}]]}],["$","pre",null,{"className":"overflow-x-auto p-5 text-xs leading-relaxed text-white/75 font-mono bg-[#0d0d18]","children":["$","code",null,{"children":"# model_registry.py  — load once at startup\nimport spacy\nfrom functools import lru_cache\n\n@lru_cache(maxsize=1)\ndef get_nlp_model():\n    \"\"\"Load model once; subsequent calls return cached instance.\"\"\"\n    nlp = spacy.load(\"en_core_web_sm\")\n    return nlp\n\n# In your Flask app factory:\nwith app.app_context():\n    get_nlp_model()  # warm the cache before first request"}]}]]}],["$","div","2",{"children":[null,["$","p","1",{"className":"text-white/65 text-[15px] leading-[1.85] mb-4","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Flask's application context is your friend here — warm the model during startup so the first real user request doesn't pay the load penalty."}}]]}]]}]]}],["$","section","4. Error Handling is Part of the Feature",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-5 leading-snug","children":"4. Error Handling is Part of the Feature"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","div","0",{"children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"text-white/65 text-[15px] leading-[1.85] mb-4","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"NLP APIs receive the worst inputs imaginable: emoji-only text, 40,000-word pastes, binary garbage encoded as UTF-8. Build for it."}}],null]}],["$","div","1",{"className":"relative my-6 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden border border-white/8","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-1.5 px-4 py-2.5 bg-white/4 border-b border-white/6","children":[["$","span","0",{"className":"w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full","style":{"background":"#ff5f56"}}],["$","span","1",{"className":"w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full","style":{"background":"#ffbd2e"}}],["$","span","2",{"className":"w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full","style":{"background":"#27c93f"}}]]}],["$","pre",null,{"className":"overflow-x-auto p-5 text-xs leading-relaxed text-white/75 font-mono bg-[#0d0d18]","children":["$","code",null,{"children":"class NLPError(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, message: str, code: int = 400):\n        self.message = message\n        self.code = code\n\n@app.errorhandler(NLPError)\ndef handle_nlp_error(e):\n    return {\"error\": e.message, \"code\": e.code}, e.code\n\ndef validate_input(text: str) -> str:\n    if not text or not text.strip():\n        raise NLPError(\"Input text cannot be empty\")\n    if len(text) > 10_000:\n        raise NLPError(\"Text exceeds maximum length of 10,000 characters\")\n    return text.strip()"}]}]]}],["$","div","2",{"children":[null]}]]}]]}],["$","section","5. Measure Everything — Latency Is a Feature",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-5 leading-snug","children":"5. Measure Everything — Latency Is a Feature"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","div","0",{"children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"text-white/65 text-[15px] leading-[1.85] mb-4","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Wrap your inference calls with timing middleware from day one. You cannot optimize what you do not measure."}}],null]}],["$","div","1",{"className":"relative my-6 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden border border-white/8","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-1.5 px-4 py-2.5 bg-white/4 border-b border-white/6","children":[["$","span","0",{"className":"w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full","style":{"background":"#ff5f56"}}],["$","span","1",{"className":"w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full","style":{"background":"#ffbd2e"}}],["$","span","2",{"className":"w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full","style":{"background":"#27c93f"}}]]}],["$","pre",null,{"className":"overflow-x-auto p-5 text-xs leading-relaxed text-white/75 font-mono bg-[#0d0d18]","children":["$","code",null,{"children":"import time\nfrom functools import wraps\n\ndef timed(fn):\n    @wraps(fn)\n    def wrapper(*args, **kwargs):\n        start = time.perf_counter()\n        result = fn(*args, **kwargs)\n        elapsed_ms = int((time.perf_counter() - start) * 1000)\n        # attach to result or log\n        return result, elapsed_ms\n    return wrapper\n\n@timed\ndef run_inference(text: str) -> dict:\n    nlp = get_nlp_model()\n    doc = nlp(text)\n    return extract_features(doc)"}]}]]}],["$","div","2",{"children":[null,["$","p","1",{"className":"text-white/65 text-[15px] leading-[1.85] mb-4","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"Log every request with its latency. When a model update ships and p99 latency doubles, you'll be glad you did."}}]]}]]}]]}],["$","section","Closing Thoughts",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-5 leading-snug","children":"Closing Thoughts"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","div","0",{"children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"text-white/65 text-[15px] leading-[1.85] mb-4","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"The gap between a demo NLP app and a production NLP service is mostly discipline, not magic. Define contracts, compose pipelines, load models once, handle failures gracefully, and measure everything. The models are the easy part — the engineering is what ships."}}]]}]]}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-white/8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-start sm:items-center justify-between gap-4","children":[["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm font-semibold text-white/70","children":"Harshita Rajput"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-xs text-white/35 mt-0.5","children":"AI Engineer · R&D at CertifyMe"}]]}],["$","$L8",null,{"href":"/#blog","className":"text-sm font-medium transition-colors","style":{"color":"#ff4d6d"},"children":"← More articles"}]]}]]}]]}]
